.TH "n_hdlc_tty_poll" 9 "n_hdlc_tty_poll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
n_hdlc_tty_poll \- TTY callback for poll system call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "__poll_t" n_hdlc_tty_poll
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "poll_table *wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
pointer to tty instance data
.IP "filp" 12
pointer to open file object for device
.IP "wait" 12
wait queue for operations
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determine which operations (read/write) will not block and return info
to caller.
Returns a bit mask containing info on which ops will not block.
